    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3865224033" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3865224033" />
    <a title="Fizz" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/57665961-fizz"><img alt="Fizz" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1627021241p2/57665961.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3865224033?book_show_action=true">Mar 14, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Fizz" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Fizz" href="/user/show/57665961-fizz">Fizz</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
                  <em>
                    This review has been hidden because it contains spoilers. To view it,
                    <a href="#" onclick="Effect.toggle(&#39;reviewTextContainer3865224033&#39;); return false;">click here.</a>
                  </em>
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3865224033" class="readable"
                    style="display:none"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7957955179939605716">&quot;𝒀𝒐𝒖𝒓 𝒍𝒊𝒗𝒆𝒔 𝒘𝒆𝒓𝒆𝒏&apos;𝒕 𝒘𝒐𝒓𝒕𝒉 𝒕𝒘𝒐 𝒑𝒊𝒄𝒆 𝒘𝒉𝒆𝒏 𝒚𝒐𝒖 𝒔𝒉𝒐𝒘𝒆𝒅 𝒐𝒇𝒇 𝒘𝒊𝒕𝒉 𝒕𝒉𝒂𝒕 𝒈𝒖𝒏.&quot;<br/><br/>This book started with one of my favourite verses from Iqbal&apos;s &quot;Shikwa&quot; (Complaint to God) so I knew I had to read it!<br/>Historical Fiction is one of my favourite genres so this review is bound to be a little biased.<br/><br/>The book shows the partition of India through the eyes of a child and I loved that we had a female protagonist for this even though it gets very overwhelming (read the trigger warnings!) This book covered many importa</span>
  <span id="freeText7957955179939605716" style="display:none">"𝒀𝒐𝒖𝒓 𝒍𝒊𝒗𝒆𝒔 𝒘𝒆𝒓𝒆𝒏'𝒕 𝒘𝒐𝒓𝒕𝒉 𝒕𝒘𝒐 𝒑𝒊𝒄𝒆 𝒘𝒉𝒆𝒏 𝒚𝒐𝒖 𝒔𝒉𝒐𝒘𝒆𝒅 𝒐𝒇𝒇 𝒘𝒊𝒕𝒉 𝒕𝒉𝒂𝒕 𝒈𝒖𝒏."<br /><br />This book started with one of my favourite verses from Iqbal's "Shikwa" (Complaint to God) so I knew I had to read it!<br />Historical Fiction is one of my favourite genres so this review is bound to be a little biased.<br /><br />The book shows the partition of India through the eyes of a child and I loved that we had a female protagonist for this even though it gets very overwhelming (read the trigger warnings!) This book covered many important points like social marginalization, loss, political bs and gender issues with just the right amount of coming-of-age narrative. I do not know why I haven't read more of Bapsi Sidhwa's work :')<br /><br />Ayyah remains my favourite character and I'm not getting over Lenny's parents and how stupidly irresponsible they were anytime soon. History nerds, worth a read!</span>
  <a data-text-id="7957955179939605716" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


