<div id="review_3307029287" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3307029287" />
    <a title="Gloria" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/100869051-gloria"><img alt="Gloria" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3307029287?book_show_action=true">Apr 28, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Gloria" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Gloria" href="/user/show/100869051-gloria">Gloria</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title=" " href="/book/show/94736.Ice_Candy_Man">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3307029287" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8486417082998164969">As a Pakistani, I have been studying the partition and pre-partition history of the sub-continent since I started school, but never was I aware of such disasters that occured during the partition. Our teachers and history books used to tell us(and they still do) that we got independemce after a long era of struggle and sacrifices of our elders but those were just words that were never elaborated. After reading&quot;Ice-candy-man&quot; I realized the true horrors of what our elders actually went through(I </span>
  <span id="freeText8486417082998164969" style="display:none">As a Pakistani, I have been studying the partition and pre-partition history of the sub-continent since I started school, but never was I aware of such disasters that occured during the partition. Our teachers and history books used to tell us(and they still do) that we got independemce after a long era of struggle and sacrifices of our elders but those were just words that were never elaborated. After reading"Ice-candy-man" I realized the true horrors of what our elders actually went through(I had nightmares after reading those inhuman acts displayed by humans at the time of partition). <br />The massacres, the bloodshed and the violent acts by those people.... It shows just how humanity can be torn through with pure ignorance and bloodlust. <br />In short our history has been sugar-coated to the core and is biased, it shows just how biased a country's history can be until you decide to look at it from every angle.</span>
  <a data-text-id="8486417082998164969" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


